The paper discusses the integration of theoretical computer science, artificial intelligence, and physical and biological sciences to model the behavior of systems without estimating parameter values. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also mentions the use of Petri nets, process calculi, and constraint programming, which are related to the sub-categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.PL (Programming Languages), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI and cs.LO, followed by cs.SY, cs.PL, and cs.CE.
